node.title: Man charged after allegedly fleeing Hobart hotel quarantine during bus transfer
node.alt: The Ibis Hotel on Macquarie Street, Hobart.
node.description: Police arrest a man who escaped while being transferred between quarantine hotels in Hobart yesterday evening.
node.content: ["Police have arrested a man\u00a0who escaped while being transferred between quarantine hotels in Hobart yesterday evening.", "The 25-year-old man, who has tested negative to COVID-19,\u00a0arrived in Tasmania on October 25 as an unauthorised traveller.", "He was being transferred from the Ibis to the Travelodge at the airport\u00a0when he ran from the bus on arrival at 5pm.", "Police found him about half an hour\u00a0later, and charged him with breaching COVID-19 directions.", "Police said the man had no contact with the community and the risk of any infection, given the negative test, was low.", "He is due to appear in court later today."]
